Now I can see the full picture:

**Fix 1**: Line 80 uses `variant={ButtonVariant.plain}`. The value `plain` exists in both the old and new union types, so no code change is needed. This fix is already satisfied.

**Fix 2**: Line 77-83 shows a `<Button>` containing only `<MinusCircleIcon />` as children. Per PF v6 migration, this icon-only Button needs to move the icon to the `icon` prop and become self-closing:

```tsx
// Before:
<Button
  id={`${rowID}-${id}-delete-btn`}
  onClick={() => onDelete(id)}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
>
  <MinusCircleIcon />
</Button>

// After:
<Button
  id={`${rowID}-${id}-delete-btn`}
  icon={<MinusCircleIcon />}
  onClick={() => onDelete(id)}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
/>
```

After this change, I need to check if `MinusCircleIcon` is still referenced — yes, it's used in the `icon` prop, so the import stays.

